733
00:55:28,030 --> 00:55:30,235
Item two, report on credit recovery.

734
00:55:30,817 --> 00:55:34,245
Madam Mayor, making a second appearance on credit recovery.

735
00:55:34,686 --> 00:55:35,989
I might come back for a third later.

736
00:55:37,823 --> 00:55:39,584
Okay, we're kind of excited about this.

737
00:55:39,944 --> 00:55:48,126
Credit recovery, as you know, for many years has been needed by our students who want to graduate on time, who want to get promoted to the next grade.

738
00:55:48,966 --> 00:55:50,227
It's always been an option.

739
00:55:50,267 --> 00:55:56,369
The guidance departments work very hard with students to find them places to make up lost credit.

740
00:55:56,409 --> 00:56:01,650
Now, oftentimes, a student can double up on a course if they have the time in their schedule.

741
00:56:02,070 --> 00:56:04,491
They can retake a course that they perhaps have failed.

742
00:56:05,222 --> 00:56:06,404
Oftentimes, it's not an option.

743
00:56:06,444 --> 00:56:08,106
They just have too full a program.

744
00:56:08,146 --> 00:56:14,836
So we have to have something in place so they can do this credit recovery outside of the regular school schedule.

745
00:56:15,817 --> 00:56:19,863
So to date, our students have been referred

746
00:56:20,518 --> 00:56:22,740
for credit recovery to outside sources.

747
00:56:22,840 --> 00:56:24,542
Many of them go over to Somerville.

748
00:56:25,122 --> 00:56:38,515
Somerville had a credit recovery program using an online program, online courses from Edgenuity, and others have been going to online, Brigham Young University.

749
00:56:39,236 --> 00:56:42,919
And again, this is all pretty much directed by the guidance department.

750
00:56:42,939 --> 00:56:43,560
These were the two

751
00:56:44,280 --> 00:56:46,662
viable places where they could pick up the credit.

752
00:56:47,562 --> 00:56:48,943
There are some problems with that.

753
00:56:49,443 --> 00:56:55,267
We know that when they go outside and they take these courses that we're not sure the content of the courses.

754
00:56:55,347 --> 00:56:58,469
Are they really a match for what we want our students to learn?

755
00:56:58,989 --> 00:57:02,491
And of course, some of these courses are very costly to students.

756
00:57:03,072 --> 00:57:04,953
So we've been working for the past few months.

757
00:57:06,242 --> 00:57:18,113
administration, Medford High School, Medford Vocational Technical High School, and Curtis Tufts, along with guidance, to work out a solution to credit recovery that we can have as our own homegrown.

758
00:57:18,873 --> 00:57:29,763
And again, we feel that having this credit recovery, we'll be able to monitor our students' progress to really take a look and make sure that they are making up what they need to make up for content.

759
00:57:31,008 --> 00:57:35,632
We also know that the district, over the past few years, we're promoting online learning.

760
00:57:36,173 --> 00:57:46,582
Online learning is the wave of the future, and I think we all feel very strongly that every student should have an online course in high school, because in college, that's what they're doing.

761
00:57:46,962 --> 00:57:50,745
You can do whole MBA programs and doctoral programs online today.

762
00:57:51,206 --> 00:57:56,831
So it's really important that students are familiar with these particular online offerings.

763
00:57:58,127 --> 00:58:05,610
This year at summer school, we piloted online science makeup courses using the product Edmentum.

764
00:58:06,050 --> 00:58:07,871
Now, we have looked at Ingenuity.

765
00:58:08,631 --> 00:58:10,912
The curriculum directors look at these products.

766
00:58:10,952 --> 00:58:12,132
They look at the courses.

767
00:58:12,712 --> 00:58:14,013
They see if they're a match.

768
00:58:14,713 --> 00:58:17,714
And they felt that Ingenuity wasn't a great match.

769
00:58:17,934 --> 00:58:22,676
And so they went and took a look at Edmentum, which is another online offering.

770
00:58:23,336 --> 00:58:25,077
And tweaking that a little bit,

771
00:58:25,681 --> 00:58:26,982
they thought that was a better product.

772
00:58:27,042 --> 00:58:38,131
So this summer, again, Mr. Cieri looked at the science offerings and he tweaked them a little bit and our students at summer school took all their science makeup courses online.

773
00:58:38,171 --> 00:58:39,052
It worked out very well.

774
00:58:39,833 --> 00:58:40,753
There were a lot of benefits.

775
00:58:40,813 --> 00:58:48,760
So for example, when summer school ends on a certain date, these students, if they weren't quite finished with the course, could continue on until they finished.

776
00:58:48,780 --> 00:58:52,603
So there are a lot of positives with using the online learning.

777
00:58:53,557 --> 00:59:04,345
So what we have done over the past few months is we've developed a protocol for credit recovery, because we want our students to stay with us as they make their credits up.

778
00:59:05,025 --> 00:59:09,889
And the terms of what we feel will work are on the next page of the report.

779
00:59:10,669 --> 00:59:21,457
We want all credit recovery courses taken through the Medford Public Schools, and that no outside district programs will be accepted for credit recovery.

780
00:59:22,502 --> 00:59:24,304
We want to keep the cost reasonable.

781
00:59:24,344 --> 00:59:25,445
Now, we looked at the cost.

782
00:59:25,485 --> 00:59:28,267
Somerville charged $125.

783
00:59:28,687 --> 00:59:31,029
Brigham Young University, I think, charged up to $350.

784
00:59:32,110 --> 00:59:33,972
So we wanted to keep it at the lower end.

785
00:59:34,452 --> 00:59:39,857
So we're going to, you know, we're thinking $125 is fair to everyone.

786
00:59:39,877 --> 00:59:42,479
Of course, if there's some hardship, we'll consider that.

787
00:59:43,520 --> 00:59:45,742
Students requesting recovery.

788
00:59:45,782 --> 00:59:49,645
There's a form that's been actually, the guidance is used for.

789
00:59:50,217 --> 00:59:53,459
several years that they have to get approval, they just can't go on their own.

790
00:59:54,479 --> 01:00:03,284
Online courses must have the endorsement of the Director of Curriculum and Instruction, Dr. Riccadeli, working with the curriculum directors, looks over all these courses.

791
01:00:03,364 --> 01:00:07,726
Now, we're not happy with all of them, so we're going to take some of them off the table for the time being.

792
01:00:08,226 --> 01:00:11,388
I know that Mrs. Joy feels Algebra I and Geometry

793
01:00:11,945 --> 01:00:24,831
through Edmentum isn't quite what it should be, so we will again offer those as credit recovery in another way for students until we can modify what's online to meet our standards.

794
01:00:25,191 --> 01:00:27,812
So we're not just putting this product out and saying this is it.

795
01:00:28,232 --> 01:00:34,415
Like Ingenuity in Somerville, they just put it out there and our kids were taking this and again, it wasn't a great match with the curriculum.

796
01:00:35,908 --> 01:00:39,389
The student liaisons, we want the students to be carefully monitored.

797
01:00:39,409 --> 01:00:48,852
And by the way, with this product in Mentum, it actually, you can see how many times a student goes online and actually engages in the learning.

798
01:00:49,372 --> 01:00:53,913
So we have the assistant principals, the guidance people that are monitoring this.

799
01:00:54,393 --> 01:01:00,995
We're gonna set up some professional development for them in January so that they know what the kids are supposed to be doing.

800
01:01:01,636 --> 01:01:02,616
And that will take place.

801
01:01:04,066 --> 01:01:06,388
We're currently making those deadlines, those arrangements.

802
01:01:07,329 --> 01:01:15,055
And then our director of instructional technology is going to maintain all records related to the use of the online courses.

803
01:01:15,595 --> 01:01:17,697
There is a cost to the online courses.

804
01:01:17,717 --> 01:01:31,067
Uh, right now we have a contract where we can have 500 courses for about $5,000, but we will recoup some of that through the tuition, both in summer school as well as the credit recovery.

805
01:01:31,801 --> 01:01:32,762
So that's our plan.

806
01:01:32,802 --> 01:01:34,564
We feel that we've made a lot of progress.

807
01:01:34,604 --> 01:01:36,106
We've had a number of meetings on this.

808
01:01:36,646 --> 01:01:41,332
We didn't like the fact our kids were going outside and we had no idea how that was going.

809
01:01:41,432 --> 01:01:44,375
They'd just come back and they'd say, this is my credit.

810
01:01:44,936 --> 01:01:46,197
We feel this is a better way to go.

811
01:01:46,217 --> 01:01:50,642
This would be just for juniors and seniors right now because we really need to work out

812
01:01:51,356 --> 01:02:00,638
the Algebra I and the Geometry, which the underclassmen tend to need, but we will have something up and running for them, probably a hybrid of this online program.

813
01:02:01,319 --> 01:02:03,819
So that's where we are, and I'd be happy to take any of your questions.

814
01:02:04,599 --> 01:02:06,460
